{
  "doc_id": "34072",
  "text": "Antiplatelet agents were not associated with an increased risk of ICH recurrence in 27 patients of 127 survivors of lobar ICH (hazard ratio [HR] 0.8, 95 % CI 0.3 to 2.3, P =0.73) [CITATION_1] . However, an increased risk of ICH has been seen with aspirin use in patients with CAA-related lobar ICH and higher numbers of cerebral lobar microbleeds [CITATION_2] . Aspirin and other antiplatelet use should be considered cautiously and avoided in those at low risk of thromboembolic events, such as in primary prevention [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
